# Business Rules

## Purpose
Align features with revenue, conversion, retention per `docs/BUSINESS_RULES.md` and CEO framework in `docs/PLAN.md`.

## Requirements
- Enforce domain rules in service layer with coded rule IDs (BR-*).
- Before new features: pass ROI checklist (revenue, conversion, productivity, retention, SEO).
- MVP scope: Phases 1-4 + partial 5; defer AI/Chat/Billing until post-MVP unless blocking sale.
- Indian market defaults: INR, +91 phone, Asia/Kolkata timezone, TRAI considerations for AI.

## Restrictions
- No feature shipping without corresponding BUSINESS_RULES or PRD update.
- No custom one-off logic for single tenant in core codebase.

## Best Practices
- Reference rule ID in exception messages for support (`BUSINESS_RULE_VIOLATION: BR-C03`).
- Unit test each BR-* rule in module tests.
- Reject scope that fails all six CEO questions.

## Anti-Patterns
- "Quick hack" bypassing duplicate detection or quota limits.
- Building MLS integrations before core pipeline works.

## Examples

```typescript
if (dto.stage.is_won && !inquiry.properties.length && !dto.no_property_reason) {
  throw new BusinessRuleViolationException('BR-C03', 'Closed Won requires linked property or reason');
}
```
